                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Inside of the heart of a played female</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>1</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>0</span>
                      /
                      <span>0</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2005-03-31</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Boooooooooring! Homechick tripped me out, sharing her lewd fantasies with the world. It was plain to me that Pac used her as a distraction while behind bars. If she wasn't beautiful he wouldn't have given her and her letter the time of day. And his constant requests for more pictures...what do you think he was doing with them??? Why didn't he try to make something happen with her upon his release? In the media I've heard about his relationship with Jada and even Keshia is mentioned. But no word of any Angela. She was straight up used and played. Maybe she thought having "exclusive" Tupac letters made her special but the book only served to bring to light how foolish she was.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Another side of Tupac was shown</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>0</span>
                      /
                      <span>0</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2005-03-23</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I think that this book was very well written and extremely honest.  I think that it reflected the mind set of both Tupac and Angela and it showed that neither of them were under the impression that they were eachothers ultimate loves.  They had a connection and he appealed to her senses and longings and she appealed to his situation and held him down mentally getting him through one day at a time with her poems and letters. I'm glad I bought this book because being such a huge Tupac fan, it gave me a side of him I had never seen and it was him telling me through his letters and poetry and not Angela telling me anything about him.  She's very talented and I commend her for sharing such private information with the world.  Information that none of us who read it would have ever seen or known had she not shared her letters. I e-mailed her to let her know what I thought and to my surprise, she e-mailed me back. She's as cool as she was in the book. It was two gemini's expressing fantasy with eachother at a time when they both needed it. Everyone should e-mail her and ask her anything you want to know at www.AngelaArdis.com, she will answer back, just like Tupac did for her. (smile) I highly recommend this book 2 all his fans and those who are just curious.
<br />
<br />Trinity
<br /></span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">The Book was cool BUt...</div>
